= Calculus

== Fundamental Theorem

Let $f$ be continuous on $[a, b]$. Define $F(x) = integral_a^x f(t) dif t$. Then:

$
  F'(x) = f(x)
$

and

$
  integral_a^b f(x) dif x = F(b) - F(a)
$

== Integration by Parts

For differentiable $u$ and $v$:

$
  integral u dif v = u v - integral v dif u
$

A classic application: $integral x e^x dif x = x e^x - e^x + C$.
